Thing is a wizard being chased IS kiting he can and will try to get space between you and cast draughts or lures.<br>
<br>
A rogue being chased is just running for his life because he knows if he stops and tries to put up a fight hes as good as mannaburned and dead. This is why moving to avoid spell dmg is less viable then moving to avoid melee dmg. You can move to avoid melee dmg 100% of the time between casts and still fight.  We melees have to stick it out and stay close and try to interupt or else flee.  Moving to avoid nukes is only a strategy to avoid getting nuked before you can close the distance and start beating on the caster.  Clear enough yet?<br>
